American Motors Corppresident Joseph E. Cappy, in a telegram to dealers, saidChrysler Corp will retain American Motors' plans to beginselling four new cars within the next year.    Cappy reassured dealers that American Motors, if it isacquired by Chrysler, would go ahead with plans to introducethe "Medallion", "Premier", Premier "X59" coupe, and the"Alpine" models.    Cappy, in a statement, said American Motors' board metyesterday on the Chrysler buyout, and will meet "periodicallyover the next several weeks on the Chrysler proposal." No otherdetails of the Chrysler takeover were disclosed.    American Motors did not release further details ofChrysler's plans for maintaining or changing American Motors'current strategy other than to quote Cappy as saying, "we willtry to keep you informed as developments warrant." Reuter&#3;